From: Christian Kastner <ckk@debian.org>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 22:19:35 +0200
Subject: Flush the log before exiting

The reproducible builds effort discovered that on certain arm64 hosts,
messages logged with LOG() did not make it to stdout.
---
 common/arg.cpp | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/common/arg.cpp b/common/arg.cpp
index c5cd4ea..f817d96 100644
--- a/common/arg.cpp
+++ b/common/arg.cpp
@@ -1071,6 +1071,7 @@ bool common_params_parse(int argc, char ** argv, common_params & params, llama_e
             if (ctx_arg.print_usage) {
                 ctx_arg.print_usage(argc, argv);
             }
+            common_log_flush(common_log_main());
             exit(0);
         }
         if (ctx_arg.params.completion) {
